OL,3,CFamily speak at inquest of 'beautiful
OL,4,Csoul' who died after care failure
OL,6,FThe family of a Jersey man who died
OL,7,Fafter his care breached health and
OL,8,Fsafety law say he will "never see his
OL,9,Fdreams come to fruition".
OL,11,FFrazer Irvine, 39, died in March 2022
OL,12,Ffrom a cardiac arrest, whilst under
OL,13,Fthe care of ambulance technician Tom
OL,14,FLe Sauteur and paramedic John
OL,15,FSutherland.
OL,17,FAt the inquest on Tuesday 10 June, Mr
OL,18,FIrvine's mother described what she
OL,19,Fcalled the privilege of being his
OL,20,Fparent.
